parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake fluid dripping from the rear of the vehicle
ABS activates at low speeds
brake lines are severely rusted and leaking fluid
brake pads and rotors are pitted and grooved.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of brakes without warning can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle fails to stop
brake failure occurs without warning lights or indications.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake system components can cause brake failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake lines are severely rusted
brake fluid is leaking
brake pads and rotors are pitted and grooved
ABS activates at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure due to Design or Material Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake system components due to design or material defects can cause brake failure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake lines are prone to corrosion
aluminum disc is insufficient
brake pads and rotors are pitted and grooved.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Loss of Power and Stalling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of power and stalling can cause accidents, especially when driving on busy roads or intersections, as the vehicle may suddenly slow down or stall without warning.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
often when accelerating from a stop
turning a corner
or driving at low speeds; the "Reduced Engine Power" warning light appears on the dashboard; the vehicle's speed is limited to 30-40 mph; the traction control system activates
causing the vehicle to lose speed; the brakes may become stiff or make a grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic traction control system can cause accidents, especially when driving on busy roads or intersections, as the vehicle may suddenly slow down or stall without warning.
symptoms: The traction control system activates randomly

causing the vehicle to lose speed; the vehicle stalls or hesitates when starting from a stop; the "Traction Active" warning light appears on the dashboard; the brakes may become stiff or make a grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electronic stability control issues can cause accidents, especially when driving on busy roads or intersections, as the vehicle may suddenly lose control or stability.
symptoms: The electronic stability control system activates and deactivates randomly; the vehicle's stability is affected
making it difficult to control; the "Traction Active" warning light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of power, stalling, or inability to shift gears, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. It can also lead to costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: Loss of power
stalling
inability to shift gears
slipping or hesitation when shifting
unusual noises or vibrations
warning lights or error messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Spongy or soft brake pedal
brake pedal traveling to the floorboard
brake fluid leaks
unusual noises or vibrations when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shifting issues can cause loss of control, stalling, or accidents.
symptoms: Transmission shifting into neutral or park while driving
inability to shift into gear
sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear differential failure can cause loss of power, stalling, or accidents, as well as costly repairs.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations
foul odors or smells
difficulty shifting gears
loss of power or acceleration.
